{"type":"message","id":"24aed723","parentId":"c007acb6","timestamp":"2026-04-12T03:19:51.886Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It seems that I don't have access to perform the `web_search` operation at this time. This function relies on the Brave Search API, which requires a special API key for authentication.\n\nTo proceed with searching for latest AI news related to LLMs, RL, diffusion models, VLMs, and robotics from the last 24 hours, I would need to configure my environment to include this API key.\n\nHere are the steps you can follow:\n\n1. Open your terminal.\n2. Run the following command:\n   ```\n   openclaw configure --section web\n   ```\n\nThis will prompt you to enter the Brave Search API key. After entering it, the configuration is saved in the Gateway environment variables, which allows me to use this feature without needing to specify the key again.\n\nOnce you've set up the API key using `openclaw configure`, I'll be able to perform the web_search operation successfully and provide you with a summary of the latest AI news as requested."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8892,"output":201,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9093,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775963991884}}
